title: Grateful Dead Live at Nassau Coliseum on 1981-05-09
description: Mississippi Half Step-> Franklin's Tower-> Feel Like A Stranger, Bird Song-> Little Red Rooster, Candyman, Mama Tried-> Mexicali Blues, Looks Like Rain-> China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Ship of Fools, Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Drums-> Nobody's Fault But Mine-> Truckin'-> Black Peter-> Around & Around-> One More Saturday Night, E: Brokedown Palace

reviews.review_text: this one sounds better - great show

Good Show Always love Half Step > Franklin’s openers. And this has an added treat of the Stranger segue.  It’s a good show.  Very collectible.  I typically keep matrixes when I can.  But Jerry’s singing is only marginal during this run, with the eighth being the worst.  So I decided to go with this AUD.

With the fidelity of this capture being the best of the bunch, Birdsgosouth is correct - "this one sounds better." My only complaint is a little signal loss and loss of the high end at the beginning of Half Step.  This is not unusual for old tapes.  It’s just unfortunate here.

I used the Mark Severson, Charlie Miller, Scott Clugston audience upload for the encore and break between so I could slowly fade out Black Peter and mix it into the cheering.  The end of the show is sweet when eliminating R&R and OMSN and fading in Brokendown.  But that’s my taste.
